Server Creation - Nodejs + Express

Basic commands
------------------

1)Creating package .json - npm init
2)Creating node modules - npm i express(install express)
3)Install nodemon - npm install -g nodemon
4)Run - nodemon index.json


Basic steps
----------------

1)Creating a folder (BankServer)
2)Create package.json file
3)Install express
4)import express inside the index.js file
5)Create an app using express
6)Setup the port number
7)Resolving the http request

8)HTTP Response code
      1xx-Information
      2xx-successful
      3xx-Redirection
      4xx-client server
      5xx-server error

9)JWT Token
Install JWT token - npm i jsonwebtoken
To Generate Token - sign()

10) Middleware
         It comes in the middle of the request and the response cycle of the nodejs execution
       req,res,next

       1)Application Specific Middleware- For entire application.
       2)Router Specific Middleware- For token verification- verify().